text: Nott Corona is a corona, a geological formation in the shape of a crown, located on the planet Venus at -32.3° N and 202° E. It is located in the Isabella quadrangle. It is named after Nótt, the Scandinavian goddess of the Earth.USGS — Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature == Geography and geology == Nott Corona covers a circular area about 150 km in diameter. ==See also== *List of coronae on Venus == References == == External links == * USGS Planetary Names – Helen Planitia * NASA site devoted to the exploration of Venus Category:Surface features of Venus
